cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with recognizing Arabic text in videos and natural scenes, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) domains. The paper also synthesizes Arabic text images, which involves generating images using machine learning techniques and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) domain. Additionally, the paper establishes baseline results for a new Arabic scene text dataset, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) domains. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
